<plot>Shpittsburgh has a really BIG problem. Something's wrong with Agent Emes, and it could not have come at a worse time. Dr. Lo-Tov is threatening to disrupt Passover. Tov Me'od headquarters must enlist the services of renowned rabbi and psychologist Abraham J. Twerski to find out what's wrong with the 12-year-old secret agent. Dr. Twerski's insights help uncover the source of our hero's malaise, but not before revealing a far greater threat to Shpittsburgh. Agent Emes is back on his feet, and now must confront a huge, unexpected menace. This menace can only be defeated with special insight into the deeper meaning of the Torah's command to eat matza on Passover.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?025795</url></doc>
